li.p:
\theta \amp = 180\degree + \widetilde{\theta}
        \amp = 180\degree + 51.3\degree = 231.3\degree
    Both angles are shown above. You can check that the cosines of 128.7\degree and 231.3\degree are both approximately -0.625.

